HEADWORD: Perilymph
<hw>Per"i*lymph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The fluid which surrounds the membranous labyrinth of the internal
ear, and separates it from the walls of the chambers in which the
labyrinth lies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perilymphangial</ent>⟦br⟧
